# Task 02 - Titanic Dataset Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)

## Objective

Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) on the Titanic dataset to understand passenger demographics and identify factors that influenced survival outcomes.

## Tool Used

* Tableau

## Dataset

Titanic Dataset

## Dashboard Highlights

* Survival Count Analysis
* Survival by Gender
* Passenger Class vs Survival
* Age Distribution
* Fare Distribution
* Age vs Fare Analysis

## Key Insights

* A larger number of passengers did not survive compared to those who survived.
* Survival rates varied significantly between male and female passengers.
* Passenger class had a noticeable impact on survival outcomes.
* Most passengers belonged to a specific age group, as observed in the age distribution.
* Fare distribution showed that a majority of passengers paid lower fares, while a smaller group paid significantly higher fares.
* Age and fare analysis helped identify patterns between passenger demographics and ticket pricing.

## Outcome

Developed an interactive Tableau dashboard to explore and visualize important trends in the Titanic dataset, providing meaningful insights into passenger survival patterns and demographic characteristics.
